               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-144v: Psalter, Dawit, ዳዊት፡. The midpoint of the Psalms (<locus target="#64v">64v, </locus>) is marked with a symbol and a text in the right margin, መንፈቀ ዳዊት. Psalm 151 is the short version. Song of Songs is the Common version. Praises of Mary begins on Monday and culminates on Sunday. F. i r: scrawls and pen trial, using the opening prayer to the Psalms. F. iii v: Prayer to Mary and David, written in pencil in an untrained hand. F. iv r: Notice of scribe: "ወልደ ገብርኤል, scribe, is the owner of this Dawit." <locus target="#144v">144v</locus> mentions the scribe, ገብረ ማርያም. The final folios were once covered with text, but are now indecipherable.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
